==English==
===Etymology===
Metaphor first recorded in 1984. Derivative from "[[nose candy]]"? (first used in 1930).
===Noun phrase===
'''eye candy'''
#''(US slang)'': A very attractive member of the opposite sex, i.e. pleasing to one's eye.  Generally has a strong sexual connotation.
#:''I'm going to the beach to check out some '''eye candy'''.''